message.content: Most men in Panama tend to have negative opinions about divorce. They often view it as a failure or a sign of weakness in a marriage. Many men believe that divorce disrupts the stability of the family and the well-being of children. They may associate divorce with financial burden and fear the implications it might have on their personal and social lives. Overall, there is a prevalent belief among men in Panama that divorce should be avoided and that couples should work through their problems instead.
